main.title: Collections
main.subtitle: Collections are containers that hold groups of related entries. Each entry in a collection can represent a blog post, product, recipe.
main.content:
Overview

Collections are simply containers that hold entries. You can think of them like box containing old pictures, except they're folders on your server and they're holding text documents. 

A collection is defined by a JSON file stored in the content/collections directory. All accompanying entries will be stored in a sub-directory with a matching name. For example, a blog collection looks like this:

Entries

Each entry — at the very least — has a title, id, and probably some content. The content fields are determined by one or more templates set on the collection.

Entries are stored as JSON files inside their collection's respective directory (content/collections/{collection}/entry.json). At any time you can edit any entry in your code editor by popping open these files and doing what comes naturally.

Templates

Each Collection uses templates to define the available fields when creating and editing its entries.

If you don't explicitly create a blueprint, your entries will have a basic set of fields: title, content, slug, etc. Of course, you're able to create your own.
